# Async HTTP Api for OCRmyPDF

# Project Overview

This project is a production-ready, Kubernetes-deployable, application with:

- Backend: Python 3.13 using FastAPI (async-first design)
- Deployment: Docker + Kubernetes
- Operation mode: Must support fully offline / air-gapped environments

This API enables integration of the popular and great working library ocrmypdf for python into modern and cloud-native
workflows and infrastructures.

---

# Core Architectural Principles

1. Async-first backend (FastAPI async endpoints everywhere).
2. Strict environment-based configuration (no hardcoded values).
3. Offline-capable deployment.
4. Kubernetes-native design.

---

# Backend Requirements (FastAPI)

## Python Version

Python 3.13 required.

## Async Requirements (MANDATORY)

- All endpoints must be async.
- ocrmypdf lib usage must be async.
- No blocking I/O inside request handlers.
- Use async file iteration when possible.


## Example usage

- integration into automation tools such as Apache NiFi through InvokeHTTP
- call from N8N Workflows to get readable PDFs


## other

- if there are useful paramaters for ocrmypdf operations, we should enable access to those through optional query params
- this project is open-source on Github. So commit messages and releases should be well written, README.md should be 
nice to read and enable easy access to get started (e.g. using Docker). 
- we will also use github actions to build releases